dismissalComment.html: he comes round the wicket and bowls a full delivery on the pads and Rohit flicks it beautifully to fine leg where the fielder takes a forward diving catch. dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni run out (sub [MC Henriques]/†Haddin) 62 (38b 7x4 2x6 73m) SR: 163.15

dismissalComment.html: full delivery on the pads and he flicks it to deep square leg and Dhoni calls for a couple, but there is none there.. He is out of the last ball to end the madness that has prevailed in the last few overs..

Dhawan's gone! Doherty has struck here. He's not been flighting the ball much and pitched this one around middle from round the wicket and the ball turned into the batsman after pitching. He played across the line and missed it, plumb he was!

Doherty gets another left-hander lbw! Pitched it on length on middle, Raina put his right foot forward to defend and there's where the ball hit him, it would have hit the stumps and Raina is unhappy wit the decision for some reason

oh this is unbelievable by Haddin and Yuvraj doesn't get any respite! It was a fuller length delivery widish outside off, Yuvraj goes for a loose drive without getting anywhere near the line, gets a thick edge that Haddin plucks off his left hand with a quick reflex dive .. Stunning catch. He turns and hurls the ball in the air

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli run out (Coulter-Nile/†Haddin) 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Kohli is run out for a duck!! It was a touch fuller as Kohli drove it down towards mid-on and set off for the single. Rohit also started but said no a little too late and by then Kohli was a long way down. The fielder throws it to the keeper and bails are off with Kohli way out of his ground. Australia now have two big wickets in the bag

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey run out (Yuvraj Singh/Vinay Kumar/†Dhoni) 4 (12b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: what a run-out this is, confusion all over for Australia! Bailey put the ball away to deep midwicket with a heave, they weren't sure about the second but went for it, Haddin tries hard to make it in time at the non-striker's end but Bailey isn't making his ground at the keeper's end, he's watching what's happening at the other end halfway through the pitch. Vinay collects the ball as Haddin dives and throws it to Dhoni, Bailey is well out of his crease caught napping

dismissalText.commentary: Brad Haddin b Ashwin 40 (49b 7x4 0x6 67m) SR: 81.63

dismissalComment.html: and Haddin's scratchy innings has come to an end! Dhoni isn't sure if the bails were flicked by the ball or by his hands! But the replays show that it took the top of the off bail. Another one goes down. That hit the top of off and ricocheted on to Dhoni's grill

dismissalText.commentary: James Faulkner c Dhawan b Mohammed Shami 116 (73b 11x4 6x6 107m) SR: 158.9

commentTextItems.html: full toss gets a wicket and it's all over! It was there to be put away, Faulkner hit it a long way in the air and Dhawan ran to his right from deep midwicket to take a diving catch to finish the match

commentPostTextItems.html: That's all we have for you all today, it was great to have yo here and we'll look forward to more feedback as India head to Kolkata for the Test against West Indies and Australia will go back home for the Ashes. Till then, it's goodbye from Vishal Dikshit on behalf of Devashish and scorer Binoy George. Ta ta!

9.42pm Dhawan is being mobbed by team-mates, Dhoni uproots the stumps and runs away in celebration, Rohit gets one too as the batsmen's series comes to an end in India's favour. Faulkner was having a word with the umpires after the dismissal, he was clearly unhappy about something. Rohit left everyone in awe, no doubt, but what an effort from James Faulkner. It was his first hundred - domestic or international - and if Australia had more wickets, he would have probably taken them home.
Prabbu Raj Menon: "i cant blame pitches or small grounds ... its purely rubbish bowling by both teams"
harshit srivastava: "faulkner will be the better allrounder for ashes than others."

George Bailey: We went pretty close there but outstanding innings from Rohit. We were probably ahead at one point of time but didn't have enough wickets. Faulkner and Maxwell played excellent cameos. We knew it would be tough they are the No. 1 and it's been a wonderful series. Plenty of positives, the one-day cricket we were playing 18 months wasn't great and we are certainly on track now.

Rohit Sharma is Man of the Match and Series: I didn't really think of the 200 initially. Right from ball one I wanted to stay there. It was a small ground with a fast outfield, we knew it was going to be a big-scoring game keeping the wickets in hand. We always spoke about building small parnterhsips and we had two big ones today. It's been our strength throughout the series so it was heartening to see that. You never know, even 380 wasn't looking comfortable. Credit goes to Dhawan and Virat as well, they played very well throughout the series, we showed real character. I'm enjoying opening at the moment, just want to keep continuing and want to continue fresh. I'm looking forward to the West Indies series now and I didn't know about the 16 sixes record.

MS Dhoni: There was a moment when we were under pressure after losing 2-3 quick wickets. It became a little difficult and we wanted to sore 300 and explode from there. 383 wasn't on our mind but Rohit batted very well. This ground has the reputation for batsmen hitting more sixes than fours, especially when you see Gayle and Virat batting in the IPL. It's difficult to contain the batsmen here. Our Batting has been fantastic, openers have done very well but it would have been good if middle order got a few more runs. Apart form the one game, we scored in each and every game. We have to improve in bowling, something we wanted to do on a team level also. We have chased 350+ twice but nobody talks about the Australian bowling line-up. Fantastic series overall, Australia played very well and the wickets were good. the amount of crowd that came was fantastic.

dismissalComment.html: full delivery on the pads and he flicks it to deep square leg and Dhoni calls for a couple, but there is none there.. He is out of the last ball to end the madness that has prevailed in the last few overs..

dismissalText.commentary: Aaron Finch lbw b Mohammed Shami 5 (5b 1x4 0x6 6m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Shami strikes! Pitched it on length on middle and was heading towards the stumps as it hit Finch's pads in front of leg. The umpire's finger went up immediately but not sure if that would have hit the stumps for sure

headshotImage.caption: Phillip Hughes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Phillip Hughes player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Phillip Hughes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Phillip Hughes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Phillip Hughes c Yuvraj Singh b Ashwin 23 (33b 2x4 0x6 54m) SR: 69.69

dismissalComment.html: strikes first ball! Pitched it full on the pads, Hughes turned it to midwicket with the wrists and it's taken easily by Yuvraj out there. Dhoni almost did a 180 split by the way

dismissalText.commentary: Brad Haddin b Ashwin 40 (49b 7x4 0x6 67m) SR: 81.63

dismissalComment.html: and Haddin's scratchy innings has come to an end! Dhoni isn't sure if the bails were flicked by the ball or by his hands! But the replays show that it took the top of the off bail. Another one goes down. That hit the top of off and ricocheted on to Dhoni's grill

headshotImage.caption: Vinay Kumar player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Vinay Kumar player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Vinay Kumar player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Vinay Kumar player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey run out (Yuvraj Singh/Vinay Kumar/†Dhoni) 4 (12b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: what a run-out this is, confusion all over for Australia! Bailey put the ball away to deep midwicket with a heave, they weren't sure about the second but went for it, Haddin tries hard to make it in time at the non-striker's end but Bailey isn't making his ground at the keeper's end, he's watching what's happening at the other end halfway through the pitch. Vinay collects the ball as Haddin dives and throws it to Dhoni, Bailey is well out of his crease caught napping

headshotImage.caption: Adam Voges player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adam Voges player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Adam Voges player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adam Voges player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Adam Voges b Mohammed Shami 4 (14b 0x4 0x6 27m) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: the leg stump has been taken out! Shami gets another one! It was a nothing shot really because Voges tried to whip it to the leg side while staying back to a length delivery, it skids in, hits his pads and then takes the stumps out. He played across the line and was probably surprised by the pace on that

headshotImage.caption: Vinay Kumar player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Vinay Kumar player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Glenn Maxwell c Jadeja b Vinay Kumar 60 (22b 3x4 7x6 23m) SR: 272.72

dismissalComment.html: short delivery outside off and Maxwell in this mood was not going to leave it, he goes for the pull but doesn't get hold of it as the ball hits the top of the bat, it lobs towards Jadeja at deep midwicket who gobbles it up..

dismissalText.commentary: James Faulkner c Dhawan b Mohammed Shami 116 (73b 11x4 6x6 107m) SR: 158.9

dismissalComment.html: full toss gets a wicket and it's all over! It was there to be put away, Faulkner hit it a long way in the air and Dhawan ran to his right from deep midwicket to take a diving catch to finish the match

dismissalText.commentary: Shane Watson c Mohammed Shami b Jadeja 49 (22b 2x4 6x6 28m) SR: 222.72

dismissalComment.html: that is the end of Watson! Jadeja hurls some words at Watson's end after the wicket, totally unnecessary! Here is what happened! It was a shorter and flatter delivery on off, the batsman went for a cut, he chops it on to Dhoni's thigh and it ricochets to lob gently for the fielder at short third man. Watson wasn't sure what happened, but he has to go.

dismissalText.commentary: Nathan Coulter-Nile c Kohli b Jadeja 3 (5b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: floated wide outside off, slower and loopy, the batsman didn't have much of an option but to go through with his shot, he aims for the sight screen, but he ends up in the big palms of Kohli at long on..

milestones.description: Clint McKay and Faulkner's 115-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 88 between Shaun Marsh and Bollinger
Vinay Kumar has conceded the most runs in an innings (102) in ODIs for IND, going past Zaheer Khan's record of 88
Rohit Sharma has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (16) in ODIs for IND, going past MS Dhoni's 10
Rohit Sharma has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (144) in an innings in ODIs for IND, going past Sehwag's 142
Rohit Sharma has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (16) in ODIs, going past Shane Watson's 15

recentReportStory.subTitle: India v Australia, 7th ODI, Bangalore
recentReportStory.seoTitle: India edge sixathon with Rohit Sharma's 209
recentReportStory.summary: It is an indictment of how skewed the contest between bat and ball has become that for 2961 ODIs, no batsman broke the 200-run barrier and now three have done it in the last 467 matches

recentPreviewStory.seoTitle: Another high-scorer on cards for series decider
